<exercisegroup><introduction><p>
    Find the <m>y</m>-intercept of each exponential function and decide whether the graph is increasing or decreasing.
</p></introduction>

<exercise number="1"><statement><p><ol cols="2">
    <li><p><m>f (x) = 26(1.4)^x</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>g(x) = 1.2(0.84)^x</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>h(x)=75\left(\dfrac{4}{5} \right)^x </m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>k(x)=\dfrac{2}{3}\left(\dfrac{9}{8} \right)^x </m></p></li>
</ol>
</p></statement>
<answer><p><ol cols="2">
    <li><p><m>26</m>; increasing</p></li>
    <li><p><m>1.2</m>; decreasing</p></li>
    <li><p><m>75</m>; decreasing</p></li>
    <li><p><m>\frac{2}{3} </m>; increasing</p></li>
</ol></p></answer>
</exercise>

