<exercise number="3"><statement><p><ol label="a" cols="2">
    <li><p><m>f(x)=3^x </m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>g(x)=\left(\dfrac{1}{3} \right)^x </m></p></li>
</ol></p></statement>
<answer><p>
    <table><tabular left="minor" right="minor" top="minor" bottom="minor" halign="center"><col halign="left"/>
        <row>
            <cell><m>x</m></cell>
            <cell><m>-3</m></cell>
            <cell><m>-2</m></cell>
            <cell><m>-1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>0</m></cell>
            <cell><m>1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>2</m></cell>
            <cell><m>3</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>f(x)=3^x </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{27} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{9} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{3} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>3</m></cell>
            <cell><m>9</m></cell>
            <cell><m>27</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>g(x)=\left(\frac{1}{3} \right)^x </m></cell>
            <cell><m>27</m></cell>
            <cell><m>9</m></cell>
            <cell><m>3</m></cell>
            <cell><m>1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{3} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{9} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{27} </m></cell>
        </row>
    </tabular></table>
    <image source="images/fig-ans-4-2-3" alt="exponential growth and decay" width="35%"/>
    The two graphs are reflections of each other across the <m>y</m>-axis. <m>f</m> is increasing, <m>g</m> is decreasing. <m>f</m> has the negative <m>x</m>-axis as an asymptote, and <m>g</m> has the positive <m>x</m>-axis as its asymptote.
</p></answer>
</exercise>

