<exercise number="15"><statement><p>
    <m>f (x) = 2^{x−1}</m>, <m>~g(x) = 2^x − 1</m>
    <table><tabular left="minor" right="minor" top="minor" bottom="minor" halign="center">
        <row>
            <cell><m>x</m></cell>
            <cell><m>y=2^x</m></cell>
            <cell><m>f(x)</m></cell>
            <cell><m>g(x)</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>-2</m></cell>
            <cell><m>\hphantom{0000} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\hphantom{0000} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\hphantom{0000} </m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>-1</m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>0</m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>1</m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>2</m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
            <cell><m> </m></cell>
        </row>
    </tabular></table>
</p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
    <li><p>To evaluate <m>f</m> we subtract <m>1</m> from the input before evaluating the exponential function; to evaluate <m>g</m> we subtract <m>1</m> from the output of the exponential function.</p></li>
    <li><p>
    <table><tabular left="minor" right="minor" top="minor" bottom="minor" halign="center">
        <row>
            <cell><m>x</m></cell>
            <cell><m>y=2^x</m></cell>
            <cell><m>f(x)</m></cell>
            <cell><m>g(x)</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>-2</m></cell>
            <cell><m>\dfrac{1}{4} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\dfrac{1}{8} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\dfrac{-3}{4} </m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>-1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>\dfrac{1}{2} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\dfrac{1}{4} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\dfrac{-1}{2} </m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>0</m></cell>
            <cell><m>1 </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\dfrac{1}{2} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>0 </m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>2 </m></cell>
            <cell><m>1 </m></cell>
            <cell><m>1 </m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>2</m></cell>
            <cell><m>4 </m></cell>
            <cell><m>2 </m></cell>
            <cell><m>3 </m></cell>
        </row>
    </tabular></table>
        <image source="images/fig-ans-4-2-15" alt="two shifts of growth" width="35%"/>
    </p></li>
    <li><p>The graph of <m>f</m> is translated <m>1</m> unit to the right; the graph of <m>g</m> is shifted <m>1</m> unit down.</p></li>
</ol></p></answer>
</exercise>

